## 2. Onboarding Checklist for Teams

### For the Owner/Admin (License Allocation)
1. Log in to the **GitLab Customers Portal** and purchase your Duo Pro seats.
2. Navigate to your top-level **Group**.
3. Go to **Settings > Usage Quotas > GitLab Duo** (or **Seats** tab).
4. Click **Add Seats** and assign licenses to your developers' usernames.
5. Go to **Settings > General**, expand **Permissions and group features**, and ensure **Experiment and Beta features** or **GitLab Duo features** are enabled.

### For the Project Maintainer (Repository Setup)
1. Go to your project repository's homepage.
2. Select **Settings > General** from the left sidebar.
3. Expand **Permissions, LFS, visibility**.
4. Locate the **GitLab Duo** or **AI features** toggle, turn it **On**, and save changes. See the [Control GitLab Duo Availability Guide](https://gitlab.com) for details.

### For the Developer (IDE Connection)
1. Open your IDE's extension marketplace (VS Code, JetBrains, or Visual Studio).
2. Install the **GitLab Workflow** extension.
3. Generate a Personal Access Token (PAT) with `api` and `read_user` scopes.
4. Authenticate the extension using your token.
5. Verify setup by checking the GitLab icon or status bar in the bottom right corner of the IDE. Detailed configurations can be found in the [GitLab Code Suggestions Setup Documentation](https://gitlab.com).

