## 3. Workflow: Code Reviews for Unlicensed Teams

If your development team does not have individual Duo Pro seats, they can still open Merge Requests (MRs) and have their code reviewed by your Duo Pro capabilities. 

### Option A: The Native Project Setting (No Code Needed)
As a Maintainer, you can enforce automatic, repository-wide AI reviews:
1. Navigate to your project's **Settings > Merge requests**.
2. Scroll to the **GitLab Duo Code Review** section.
3. Check **"Enable automatic reviews by GitLab Duo"**.
4. Save changes.
*Result: Every time an unlicensed dev opens an MR, GitLab Duo automatically performs a first-pass review. For configuration details, visit the official [GitLab Duo Code Review Guide](https://gitlab.com) and [Code Review Flow Documentation](https://gitlab.com).*

### Option B: The Automated Pipeline Trigger (`.gitlab-ci.yml`)
If your organization requires initiating this via a CI/CD pipeline, you can pass a custom API request. Save your Maintainer PAT (which holds the Duo Pro license) as a masked, protected CI/CD variable named `GITLAB_API_TOKEN`.

Add the following to your pipeline configuration:
```yaml
stages:
  - automation

trigger_duo_review:
  stage: automation
  image: curlimages/curl:latest
  script:
    - |
      echo "Triggering GitLab Duo review via Quick Action API..."
      curl --request POST \
        --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: \${GITLAB_API_TOKEN}" \
        --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
        --data "{\"body\": \"/assign_reviewer @GitLabDuo\"}" \
        "\${CI_API_V4_URL}/projects/\({CI_PROJECT_ID}/merge_requests/\){CI_MERGE_REQUEST_IID}/notes"
  rules:
    - if: '\$CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == "merge_request_event"'
```

### Directing the AI's Behavior
You can dictate exactly how Duo reviews your team's code by adding a file named `.gitlab/duo/mr-review-instructions.yaml` to the root of your repository:
```yaml
instructions:
  - instruction_name: "Check security and style"
    prompt: "Ensure no hardcoded API keys are present and code follows standard naming conventions."
```
*Note: To link this config file globally to your team, map it inside your group portal by following the [Customizing Review Instructions Guide](https://gitlab.com).*

